  Audit findings classified and incorporated

  Finding 1: INDEX.md has 8 wrong sizes → FIX-009

  All 8 deltas verified against VERIFICATION_MANIFEST.json (the
  authoritative source with actual size_bytes fields). The largest
  errors: CONTRACT_GAP_MATRIX.md claimed ~42KB but is 15.4KB;
  remediation_plan.json claimed ~8KB but is 1.7KB. These are
  pre-execution estimates that were never updated against actual output.

  Finding 2: INDEX.md references a phantom file → FIX-009

  REMEDIATION_PLAN_SUMMARY.md is marked "To be created (optional)" — it
  was never created. The plan requires removing or explicitly marking it
   NOT_CREATED.

  Finding 3: INDEX.md missing 9 rewrite-delivery files → FIX-009

  README.md, BEFORE_AFTER_COMPARISON.md, EXECUTION_COMPLETE.md,
  ACCEPTANCE_VALIDATION_REPORT.md, CORRECTION_REPORT.md,
  IMPLEMENTATION_CHECKLIST.md, ISSUE_REMEDIATION_PLAN.md,
  COMPLETION_CERTIFICATE.txt, and zany-napping-lollipop.md all exist on
  disk and belong to the rewrite delivery but are absent from the index.

  Finding 4: INDEX.md template path wrong → FIX-009

  newPhasePlanProcess/... → ../newPhasePlanProcess/... (consistent with
  the FIX-003 repo-relative strategy already in the plan).

  Finding 5: VERIFICATION_MANIFEST.json missing 4 entries → FIX-010

  COMPLETION_CERTIFICATE.txt, REG_AUTO_PLAN.txt, ChatGPT-Automation
  Alignment Assessment.md, and zany-napping-lollipop.md all exist on
  disk but postdate the manifest's 2026-03-08T19:00:36Z creation
  timestamp. The plan adds them with actual byte sizes read from disk
  (not estimated). VERIFICATION_MANIFEST.json itself is excluded from
  self-referential entry as an acceptable gap. Target: 126 → 130
  artifacts.

  What this does NOT claim to fix

  The manifest covering 126 files vs index covering 21 paths is by
  design — the manifest covers the entire registry repository; the index
   covers only the rewrite delivery package. The plan does not attempt
  to make them match 1:1.